g: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><div style="clear:both;"></div></ul></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) left top no-repeat; display: block;"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) right top no-repeat; display: block;"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>The popularity of this model among brides is because it reflects almost all following fashion trends:</strong></p><ul><li>a delicate elastic top with embroidery;</li><li>a built-in bra or cut-off cups;</li><li>a tender silhouette of a lace dress;</li><li>an open back and a short lacing on air loops;</li><li>and a full detachable skirt with a train.</li></ul><p><strong>This course contains a lot of couture techniques. I will show you the following:</strong></p><ul><li>how to seamlessly cover the corset with lace;</li><li>how to join a lace folded skirt to a dress, so that you don’t have any extra thickness and the transition from a corset to a dress is smooth and invisible;</li><li>how to sew an elastic top between a face and a lining;</li><li>how to make a lining with built-in cups.</li></ul><p><strong>The special feature of the course is tambour (luneville) sequin embroidery.</strong></p><p>The process of cutting, sewing and decoration of a garment from scratch to final operations is described and illustrated in detail.<br> All necessary patterns and bonuses (for printing) are attached as follows:</p><ul><li>2 tables for AUTOMATIC pattern adjustments calculation for all patterns of this course;</li><li>patterns of a corset face and a corset lining;</li><li>patterns of decorative details.</li></ul><div><p><strong>The aim of the course</strong>&nbsp;is my great desire to teach the techniques of making such dresses. All the techniques can be used in various combinations, so that you can sew different models of evening, cocktail, prom and wedding dresses.</p><p><strong>The course is useful</strong>&nbsp;both to beginners as well as to experienced professionals in making wedding and evening dresses. It can be handy for dressmaking atelier personnel as a professional development training.</p></div><div></div><div><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;6h 45m</p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-3-changes-of-the-lining-pattern-for-our-client/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-3-changes-of-the-lining-pattern-for-our-client/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-12-01T12:55:13+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2018-12-01T13:05:52+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2018"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 3. Changes of the lining pattern for our client."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 3. Changes of the lining pattern for our client."><meta itemprop="description" content="I cut all 6 front pattern pieces, arranged them in a stack and prepared stack of standard lining patters for the corset."><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Wedding Dress with Detachable Full Skirt. Part 1."><meta itemprop="keywords" content="wedding dress with detachable full skirt. part 1., video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><h1>Tutorial 3. Changes of the lining pattern for our client.</h1><p><strong>I cut all 6 front pattern pieces, arranged them in a stack and prepared stack of standard lining patters for the corset. &nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image002.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>There is no change on the central face piece (piece № 1). When overlaid the central patterns of the face and the lining are similar. &nbsp;</strong>Thus, there are no alterations in the central piece of cup.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image004.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image006.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>We take the middle pieces of the face and the lining (piece №2). There were some alterations on the middle piece of the face. </strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image008.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>I overlay the middle patterns of the face and the lining and on the lining pattern I trace alterations I have made earlier on the face pattern. &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image010.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I also prolong the cup joining line. &nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image012.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Now I take the cup patterns of the lining (pieces &nbsp;№ 7 and № 8).</strong> On the side piece of the cup (piece № 8) there is a line, which joins this pattern piece with the curve line of the middle face piece of the corset.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image014.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I place the middle front pattern of the corset face over the side piece of the cup lining and draw on the cup pattern the same alteration I made on the middle piece of the face. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image016.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image018.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image020.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Please remember,</strong> the middle front piece of the corset face contains seam allowance.</p><p><strong>Thus,</strong> in order to determine the modified line of the side cup I need to shift seam allowance of 1,2 cm from the middle front curve drawn on the cup.</p><p><strong>Here I have a new joining line, shifted by 0,5cm toward center. </strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image022.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>The pattern of the side front piece (piece №3) remained unchanged from the curve line. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image024.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I place the side front piece of the corset face over the side cup piece and draw an upper edge line.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image026.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>On the upper edge of the cup a bend occurs due to alteration for 0,5 cm of clip-toward- armscye measurement. &nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image028.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>Please bear in mind, </strong>that we have additional 0,5 cm on the side cup of the lining, where the joining line between the side and the middle pieces with the curve line is shifted.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image030.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>In order to reduce the side cup of the lining for 0.5 cm you can cut the pattern along new joining line, shift it by 0,5cm and glue together. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image032.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image033.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I draw a graceful line of the upper edge of the side cup piece.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image035.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Now I start altering the side front piece of the corset lining (piece №3).</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image037.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>The pattern of the side front pieces was scaled up, thus I place the front pattern over the lining piece and draw the new modified side seam lines and the upper and the bottom edges. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image039.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Important:</strong> please remember the pattern of the side front piece of the corset face contains seam allowances, but the side lining piece does not have seam allowance on its upper edge. Thus, the height of the lining piece is changed.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image041.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>We retract 1,2 cm equal to the seam allowance on the upper edge of the side piece of the corset lining. </strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image043.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>This is how the altered pattern of the side lining pattern looks now. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image045.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>We have finished alteration of the lining front pieces, now we switch on the back pieces.&nbsp; </strong>Certainly you remember that the alterations in the side front seam were made on the back curves.</p><p><strong>We take the same steps with the side back (piece № 4):</strong> we place the side back piece of the face over it, combine and outline. We should remember that there is no seam allowance of 1,2 cm along the upper edge of the lining side piece.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image047.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image049.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image050.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>When combining the patterns of the middle back pieces of the face and the lining&nbsp; (pieces №5) we take into account that the alterations on the middle back pieces of the face were made along curves from both sides. &nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;So, we combine the common pointes of the pieces, for instance, crossing points of seam allowances. Next we draw the new curves on the middle back piece of the lining. We need to remember that there is no seam allowance along the upper edge of the lining pattern piece. Next we outline the ready pattern.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image052.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image053.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image055.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image057.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image059.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>The patterns of the central pieces of the face and the lining are almost identical (piece №6) </strong>as we have not made any alterations along the central line<strong>, </strong>but the curve line is changed. I overlay the patterns and trace the new curve line onto the back pieces of the lining.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image061.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image063.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Thus, we have a new set of patterns for the face and the lining of the corset based on the measurements of my client. &nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%203.files/image065.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>To revise our knowledge we will review one more example using the measurement of an imaginary client in our next tutorial. &nbsp;</strong></p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format. To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose&nbsp;<strong>“print in actual size”</strong>. In each&nbsp;file the pattern is divided &nbsp;to A4 paper sheets for home printers.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Automatic Pattern Alterations Calculator:</strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGcorset/corset.htm" target="_blank">The Dress (Corset)</a></strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGskirt/ENGskirt.htm" target="_blank">The Skirt</a></strong></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/belt%2C%20bow.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Belf and The Bow</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20front.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Front</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20lining.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Lining</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/pattern.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Pattern</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/skirt.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Skirt</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/top.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Top</a><br></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="diploma"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><p>In order to receive the Corset Academy graduation diploma you need to submit your graduation work.<br> Upload the photo of the garment that you made after completing the course.<br> I will personally review your work.<br> After the approval you will receive a personalized diploma to your email box, no longer than within 1 business day.</p><p class="text-right">Tatiana Kozorovitsky.</p><form id="diplomaForm"><h4>Your datails:</h4><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="firstname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter first name" required=""><p class="firstname error">Enter your first name</p></div><div 